First, we need to find the symmetric difference (Δ) between sets A and B. The symmetric difference between two sets is the set of elements which are in either of the sets but not in their intersection. 

A Δ B = (A ∪ B) - (A ∩ B)

A ∪ B = {2, 3, 4, 6, 7, 8}
A ∩ B = {4}

So, A Δ B = {2, 3, 6, 7, 8}

Now, we need to find the symmetric difference between the result (A Δ B) and set C.

(A Δ B) Δ C = ({2, 3, 6, 7, 8} Δ {4, 6, 9})

(A Δ B) ∪ C = {2, 3, 4, 6, 7, 8, 9}
(A Δ B) ∩ C = {6}

So, (A Δ B) Δ C = {2, 3, 4, 7, 8, 9}
